        "biography": {
            "errors": [],
            "value": "I have a degree in Mechanical Engineering from the Universidad Nacional San Antonio Abad del Cusco - Per\u00fa (2004). My credentials include a master's degree (2008) and doctorate degree (2013) in Mechanical Engineering from the Pontifical Catholic University of Rio de Janeiro. I participated in the postdoctoral program at the Department of Mechanical Engineering at PUC-Rio (2013-2018). I worked as a researcher at the Honeywell Research Lab laboratories. Buffalo, NY, USA (2009-2011). Currently, I am consultant I at Instituto of Technical-Scientific Software Tecgraf / PUC-Rio, developing computational models for the oil and gas industry with emphasis on multiphase reservoir simulation. I have experience in thermosciences, acting on automotive, domestic and commercial refrigeration systems, heat pumps, reciprocating compressors, two-phase and multiphase flow, heat and mass transfer, thermodynamics, fluid mechanics, nanofluids, optimization methods. (genetic algorithms) and numerical simulation.",
